  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Georgia: Promoting Trade Union Membership</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Solidarity Center conducts labor education and capacity building programs to boost awareness of worker rights as well as membership in trade unions, particularly in the railroad and education sectors. The project also provides legal guidance for workers whose rights have been violated, as well as advocates for future legislation to protect worker rights.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Solidarity Center partners with the Georgian Trade Union Confederation (GTUC) to strengthen its capacity to increase civic participation on issues affecting workers. The Solidarity Center and GTUC together work to improve the environment for working people, supporting their ability to exercise their rights, join unions and advocate for the protection of their rights as workers. Since the project began, thousands of workers have joined and become more active in trade unions.</narrative>
  </description>
